cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on using deep neural network based optical flow and single-view depth prediction methods for speed estimation of the ego-vehicle on the KITTI benchmark. This falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The speed estimation of the ego-vehicle is an important aspect in robotics, especially for autonomous vehicles. The paper discusses the limitations and future directions for this application, which is relevant to the robotics community.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep neural network based methods for speed estimation, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep neural networks for speed estimation can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The KITTI benchmark involves recordings of real-world driving scenarios, which can be considered as multimedia data. The paper discusses the use of monocular images for speed estimation, which is relevant to the multimedia community.
